s.text: The Commission's analyses use both quantifiable and general descriptions of the effects of the rule and alternatives on small entities.
The Commission determined that one part of the fee schedule--specifically, the annual fee for materials licensees--will have a significant impact on a substantial number of small entities.
The Supplementary Information published in the Federal Register with the final rule includes the full text of the Commission's final regulatory flexibility analysis.

Pursuant to section 801(a)(2)(A) of title 5, United States Code, this is our report on a major rule promulgated by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission entitled "Revision of Fee Schedules; 100% Fee Recovery, FY 1966" (RIN 3150-AF39).
